import os
import subprocess
from pathlib import Path

# Constants
base_dir = Path.home() / "aetherdev"
project_dir = base_dir / "aetherbridge"
venv_dir = project_dir / "venv"
env_file = project_dir / ".env"
requirements = [
    "fastapi", "uvicorn", "psycopg2-binary", "python-dotenv",
    "httpx", "requests", "jinja2"  # Add others as needed
]

# 1. Create venv if not exists
def setup_virtualenv():
    if not venv_dir.exists():
        subprocess.run(["python3", "-m", "venv", str(venv_dir)])
        print(" Virtual environment created.")
    else:
        print(" Virtual environment already exists.")

# 2. Install dependencies
def install_dependencies():
    pip_path = venv_dir / "bin/pip"
    subprocess.run([str(pip_path), "install", "--upgrade", "pip"])
    subprocess.run([str(pip_path), "install"] + requirements)
    print(" Dependencies installed.")

# 3. Create default .env
def write_env():
    if not env_file.exists():
        env_file.write_text("API_KEY=\nDB_URL=\n")
        print(" .env created.")
    else:
        print(" .env already exists.")

# 4. Create basic FastAPI scaffold if missing
def scaffold_api():
    main_file = project_dir / "main.py"
    if not main_file.exists():
        main_file.write_text(
            '''from fastapi import FastAPI
from fastapi.responses import JSONResponse

app = FastAPI()

@app.get("/api")
def read_root():
    return JSONResponse({"message": "AetherCore API is live"})
''')
        print(" FastAPI app scaffolded.")
    else:
        print(" main.py already exists.")

# 5. Summary
def report():
    print("\n AetherBridge is ready.")
    print("To start your server:")
    print(f"source {venv_dir}/bin/activate && uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080 --reload")

# Execute all
setup_virtualenv()
install_dependencies()
write_env()
scaffold_api()
report()
